gobblin.writer

Class MetadataWriterWrapper<D>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.writer.MetadataWriterWrapper<D>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataWriter<Object>, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class MetadataWriterWrapper<D>
extends Object
implements DataWriter<Object>
    Wraps an existing DataWriter and makes it metadata aware. This class is responsible for doing the following: 1. If the underlying writer is MetadataAwareWriter, query it to get default metadata to add to any incoming records. 2. Process each incoming record: 2a. If it is a RecordWithMetadata, process the metadata and pass either the underlying record or the RecordWithMetadata, depending on the writer class type, to the wrapped writer. 2b. If it is a standard record type attach any default metadata and pass the record to the wrapped writer. 3. On commit(), publish the combined metadata output to JobState property so it can be published.
